race.description: Nhp Electrical Engineering Products Midway Hcp  (C1)
race.comment: ROMAN FORUM (4) is a promising mare who hasn't appeared since she led all the way and just prevailed on debut over 1200m at Gosford on ANZAC Day. Trialling in great style so although longer trips will suit at some stage she looks set for a bright return. OAKFIELD SATURN (3) returns for a second campaign. Won on debut then placed in three Class 1 sprints before being turned out. Talented mare who should come to hand quickly again. GUNROOM (1) is a new acquisition for the Beer/Carpenter yard and is back from a 20-week break. Was highly competitive in town last prep without winning. Goes very fast and will probably look the winner at some stage. CAELUS (2) last appeared when third over 1400m at Hawkesbury on 3 July. Lightly raced four-year-old with plenty to offer this time in work. Market watch on the first starter THE PROSPECT (8) who placed in a recent trial at this track.
